cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving genome analysis and presents a secure logistic regression training protocol. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses logistic regression training and its implementation. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with high dimensional genome data distributed across a local area network. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is possible as the paper applies the logistic regression model to genome analysis. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also possible as the paper deals with distributed data and presents a new subprotocol for computing the activation function.
